variant.listItem:
(a) object NPs following a verb (e.g. and
have found marked changes);
(b) NPS not (directly) following a verb (e.g.
once in individual association and once in
a combine,d,fixed preparation);
(c) complex NPs (e.g. after a co-ordinating
conjunction);
(c) subject NPs at the beginning of sentence
(e.g. Affected males suffer profound
deficits ...).
